article.headline: UC Riverside 82, Cal St.-Fullerton 76
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) -- Larry Cunningham scored 34 points in the second half as UC Riverside upset Cal State Fullerton 82-76 Saturday. It was the first Big West Conference win of the season for the Highlanders (5-17, 1-7 conference). Riverside has won its last two games after struggling through a 15-game losing streak. Cunningham sparked Riverside's offense in the second half, giving the Highlanders a 61-59 lead with just under eight minutes to play. The Titans tied the score on their ensuing possession as Marcus Crenshaw hit Bobby Brown with an alley-oop pass. The Highlanders answered with a 12-2 run. The Titans managed to reduce the lead but couldn't overcome it. Frank Robinson was Fullerton's high-scorer with 18 points and teammate Justin Burns added a double-double of 14 points and 13 rebounds for the Titans (16-5, 6-3).
